Anh - Anh
septoria
[sɛp'tɔ:rɪə]
■ noun a fungus of a genus that includes many kinds that cause diseases in plants. [Genus Septoria.]
⁃ leaf spot disease caused by such a fungus.
Origin
mod. L., from L. septum (see septum).
